gomodel:SYNGO_4930  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunogold-electronmicroscopy shows goldparticles within dendritic spines and in the synaptic cleft (ticket #4931) (Fig. 2Q-V). \"Within MMP-9 - immunoreactive spines, immunogold particles were present mainly in the spine head, frequently being located adjacent to, or within, postsynaptic densities (PSD) of axospinous (excitatory) synapses (Fig. 2, Q, R, T, and U).\"\n\nFig. 3L,M shows massively enhanced MMP9 immunoreativity in spines 72hrs after treatment with kainate.. Experimental description: \"Postembedding procedure was performed according to ... In brief, normal Wistar rats were perfused...\" (p.1033)\n\nM&M:\n\"The immunoreactions consisted of sequential incubations with a rabbit anti - MMP-9 antibody (Torrey Pines Biolabs, Inc.) diluted at 1:50, followed by species-specifi c goat secondary antibodies coupled to 10-nm gold particles (GE Healthcare)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2023-10-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4930" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

